Comic-Con supervising director Dave Filoni has announced that Star Wars: The Clone Wars will return for a new season. Speaking at San Diego Comic-Con, Filoni said the new season of the show would be available on Disney’s direct-to-consumer streaming service. The season will feature 12 new episodes and will include the same cast of characters as the previous seasons. Star Wars: The Clone Wars first aired in 2008 and ran for five seasons, along with several “Lost Missions” episodes – which aired later on Netflix. The series follows the adventures of popular Star Wars characters such as Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker during the Clone Wars period. There is currently no official release date for the new season of Star Wars: The Clone Wars. 